# SPOLIA Web Development Rules

## CRITICAL: File Management Rules

- NEVER delete files without explicit user permission
- ALWAYS ask before deleting any files, even if they seem redundant
- When restructuring code, prefer creating new files over deleting existing ones
- If files need to be removed, clearly explain why and get user confirmation first

## Code Development Rules

- Always preserve existing functionality when making changes
- Test changes thoroughly before considering them complete
- Maintain consistent code style and structure
- Document any breaking changes or major modifications

## User Communication Rules

- Explain what you're doing before making significant changes
- Ask for clarification when requirements are unclear
- Provide clear summaries of what has been implemented
- Always confirm understanding of user requirements before proceeding

## File Structure Rules

- Respect the existing project structure
- When creating new features, follow established patterns
- Maintain separation of concerns (components, pages, styles)
- Keep related files organized in appropriate directories

## Error Handling Rules

- Fix errors immediately when they occur
- Provide clear error messages and solutions
- Don't leave the project in a broken state
- Test fixes to ensure they work properly

## Version Control Rules

- Make atomic commits with clear messages
- Don't mix unrelated changes in single commits
- Preserve git history when possible
- Document any major architectural changes
